          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Zn-S scintillators fixed  at  180  degrees",
                " with  respect  to each other,  were used the overall",
                " angular region being from 30  to  330  degrees.  The",
                " thickness of ZnS layer is 10-20 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The angular distribution was analysed by least square",
                " fit assuming that:",
                "      A+B*(sin(teta))**2*(1+C*cos(teta))**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "THEO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The result was compared with the theory  based",
                " on the 'two-stage mechanism'."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin foils of lithium,  sulfur,  aluminum,  nikel and",
                " copper   have   been  irradiated,  and  the  angular",
                " distribution  of  photoprotons  was  obtained.   The",
                " angular  distribution  of photoprotons thus obtained",
                " can  be  classified  into  two  broad   types,   one",
                " isotropic  and  the  other  forward asymmetric.  The",
                " angular distribution for aluminium  and  nickel  (21",
                " MeV)  belong  to  the  former  type;  while that for",
                " lithium,  sulfur,  nickel (18 MeV) and  copper  fall",
                " under  the latter type,  which is represented by the",
                " theoretical form,",
                "          A+B*sin(teta)**2*(1+C*cos(teta))**2.",
                " As an exceptional case, copper has shown an abnormal",
                " angular distribution having a maximum in the forward",
                " direction  and  also  a  rise  up  in  the  backward",
                " direction.  The functional form which fits  best  to",
                " this  distribution  has  been calculated by a bendix",
                " computer and compared  with  the  recent  theory  of",
                " photonuclear reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
